[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-08T19:33:19+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Chrome 3D wifi symbols in The Verge brand colors on a black background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Gr-HbY9Rub5VQTe2bvs7OovTZ5Y=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73640961/236811_WIFI_STOCK_CVirginia_5.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ElEyA9\">A treaty finalized by the UK may bring about the end of the .io domain. Last week, the <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/news/joint-statement-between-uk-and-mauritius-3-october-2024\">British government announced</a> that it has agreed to give up ownership of the Chagos Islands, a territory in the Indian Ocean it has controlled since 1814 \u2014 relinquishing the .io domain with it.</p>\n<p id=\"CkDF81\">But first, let\u2019s take a step back (and I mean <em>far</em> back) to see how we got here. According to the <a href=\"https://www.britannica.com/place/British-Indian-Ocean-Territory\">Encyclopedia Britannica</a>, the Chagos Island", "id": 1290619, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/8/24265441/uk-treaty-end-io-domain-chagos-islands", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How a UK treaty could spell the end of the .io domain", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-08T18:55:24+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Woman in floral dress with hand on hip modeling Apple watch SE (2022)\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/xJgi0AaTSn343xblE-2lNQRzC8Q=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73639910/226292_Apple_Watch_SE_PHO_akrales_0133.5.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Apple\u2019s entry-level smartwatch, the second-gen Apple Watch SE, is down to its best price to date.</em> | Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Dj3c3d\">If you don\u2019t want to wait until Black Friday or Cyber Monday to save big on some of Apple\u2019s most popular products, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24255302/amazon-prime-day-deals-tips-news-guide-2024-october\">Amazon\u2019s October Prime Day event</a> presents an earlier opportunity. Right now, Apple\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0D1XD1ZV3/?tag=theverge02-20\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">second-gen AirPods Pro</a> are down to their all-time low, while the <a", "id": 1290620, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24264786/apple-amazon-prime-day-deal-sale-airpods-october", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The best Apple deals available for Amazon\u2019s October Prime Day event", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-08T18:49:03+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector collage of the X logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/BbT49Ndk9DNxhn4yM1ZQldvuXf0=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73555180/STK160_X_TWITTER__C.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p>Supreme Court Justice&nbsp;Alexandre de Moraes ordered the country\u2019s telecom agency to unblock X after the company complied with court orders and paid its fines.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/30/24232573/brazil-x-twitter-ban-elon-musk\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1290621, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/30/24232573/brazil-x-twitter-ban-elon-musk", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Brazil\u2019s X ban is coming to an end: all the latest news", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-08T18:27:54+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"reddit account page for user whitehouse\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/f51hwCpmKAq9ojIe-qCbo6TR9ts=/0x0:2263x1509/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73640883/Screenshot_2024_10_08_at_5.09.48_PM.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The earliest post on the account is a picture of Biden getting briefed on the hurricanes.</em> | Screenshot: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"pMyqbZ\">Reddit isn\u2019t the first place you\u2019d think to see official statements and news coming from the federal government, but today, The White House is on the site making posts. You\u2019ll often see staffers posting on social media platforms like Instagram and X to announce updates and reach a larger audience, so this feels new. The Biden administration\u2019s \u201cwhitehouse\u201d account <a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/user/whitehouse/\">has new posts</a> in subreddits r/NorthCarolina and r/Georgia to discuss the federal response to Hurricane Helene and Hurricane Milto", "id": 1290200, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/8/24265598/white-house-official-reddit-account-posting-hurricane", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The White House started posting on Reddit to talk about Hurricane Milton", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-08T18:27:24+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector collage of the X logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/PqpLiY8HBRa5XaBdLtbPJ4UOmaw=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73640881/STK160_X_TWITTER_2__D.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"y1hjr4\">On Tuesday, Brazilian Supreme Court Justice Alexandre de Moraes <a href=\"https://noticias.stf.jus.br/postsnoticias/stf-autoriza-o-retorno-imediato-do-x-e-determina-que-anatel-adote-providencias-para-a-retomada-do-servico/\">ordered</a> the country\u2019s telecommunications agency Anatel to unblock X within 24 hours, writing that it has fulfilled \u201call the requirements necessary for the immediate return of activities. </p>\n<p id=\"cVAkD7\">However, this won\u2019t mean an immediate return to service for the app. As noted by the <a href=\"https://www.poder360.com.br/poder-justica/alexandre-de-moraes-manda-desbloquear-o-x-no-brasil/\">Brazilian outlet <em>Poder360</em></a>, Anatel still nee", "id": 1290201, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/8/24265606/x-twitter-unbanned-brazil-supreme-court", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Brazil clears X for return after a monthlong ban", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-08T17:00:45+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo of an Echo Spot sitting on a nightstand.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/nL1d_zBLRFdJqWxJp_t31Vr4D1g=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73639696/247196_Echo_Spot_Review_8A0A1511_CVirginia.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Amazon\u2019s throwing in a free smart color bulb with many of its smart speakers, including the new Echo Spot.</em> | Photo by Jennifer Pattison Tuohy / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"iZ4p4h\">Once again, Amazon is holding a second Prime Day under the guise of <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/17/24244180/amazon-october-prime-day-big-deal-days-fall-dates-2024\">Prime Big Deal Days</a>, which runs through tomorrow, October 9th. While the naming convention might be terrible, the sale isn\u2019t. In fact, many of our favorite gadgets and goods are receiving notable discounts right now, which we\u2019ve highlighted in our larger roundup of the<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/good-deals/2", "id": 1288684, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24262440/amazon-prime-day-best-cheap-tech-deals-under-50-october-2024", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The best October Prime Day deals you can get for less than $50", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-08T16:42:14+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshot of a text message sent via satellite.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/BE5Pp52zIDsQYO6UwakEJj5BKZw=/824x0:2636x1208/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73640501/Screenshot_2024_06_10_at_1.23.44_PM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Newer iPhones can communicate over satellite without Wi-Fi or cellular service.</em> | Image: Apple</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Lf6ZQU\">With <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/7/24264419/hurricane-milton-category-5-storm-rapid-intensification-climate-change\">Hurricane Milton</a> set to become the second major hurricane to hit the US in under a month, the nation\u2019s infrastructure is under strain. In the aftermath of a natural disaster, when power and cellphone service are out, connecting to 911 and friends and family from your smartphone via satellite can be a literal lifeline. </p>\n<p id=\"vnpxMN\">Apple\u2019s <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/en-us/101573\">Emergency SOS via satellite", "id": 1288685, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24265288/satellite-messages-iphone-pixel-how-to-send", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to send messages via satellite on your iPhone or Pixel", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-08T15:47:57+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"The GM logo in blue and white\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-D9tiVk66q35I7fKp_1zYl9FkJI=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73640321/acastro_STK057_02.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"wdM2JI\">GM will discontinue the Ultium battery brand name as it looks to expand the types of cells and chemistries it uses in its electric vehicles. </p>\n<p id=\"4jtcNQ\">During an investor event today, Kurt Kelty, GM\u2019s VP of batteries and a former Tesla executive, announced plans to adopt lithium iron phosphate (LFP) battery technology in order to decrease the cost of its EVs by \u201cup to $6,000.\u201d GM uses the more common nickel cobalt manganese (NCM) batteries in its Ultium platform.</p>\n<p id=\"rqaAu2\">Some automakers are using LFP-based cells already, including Tesla and <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/2/13/23597622/ford-ev-battery-factory-lfp-chemistry\">Ford", "id": 1288686, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/8/24265416/gm-ultium-ev-battery-platform-discontinued-lfp", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "GM\u2019s Ultium battery gets the ultimatum", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-08T15:25:24+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Room with neon light in majora mask shape, TV, other objects\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/BVocgiijpOw9RqPRjLq9EbjQ1qg=/0x250:1500x1250/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73639601/lights.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo: Ethereal Lomoer</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"6SIrOL\">Every month or so, we like to ask our staff <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22344288/favorite-gadgets-tech-lgear-aptops-headphones-kitchen-recommendations\">about their favorite stuff</a> \u2014 whether it\u2019s board games, smart tech, or kitchen gadgets. And the results are usually very different, very interesting, and a lot of fun.</p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang\"><aside id=\"CP4RWK\"><div data-anthem-component=\"readmore\" data-anthem-component-data='{\"stories\":[{\"title\":\"The best deals from Amazon\u2019s October Prime Day sale\",\"url\":\"https://www.theverge.com/good-deals/24262468/amazon-prime-day-best-deals-sales-tech-gadgets-october-2024\"},{\"title\":\"", "id": 1288687, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24265074/amazon-prime-day-best-deals-sale-tech-staff-picks-favorites-october-2024", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The best Prime Day deals you can get on some of our favorite gadgets ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-08T15:12:46+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot of the Mastodon Mac app redesign in dark and light mode.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/EcrJ9XiBvkYRnTz8KFalRq53-dk=/59x0:1522x975/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73640218/hero.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Mastodon is getting some much-needed tweaks.</em> | Image: Mastodon</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"gEoD4s\">Mastodon just released version 4.3 of its web app, and CEO Eugen Rochko <a href=\"https://blog.joinmastodon.org/2024/10/mastodon-4.3/\">says its new updates</a>, like grouped notifications, should make the open social network easier to use.</p>\n<p id=\"Fhf0V5\">For example, a \u201cWho to follow\u201d carousel that shows up in the home tab now recommends a mix of \u201cgeneralized results\u201d such as profiles that are popular in your language and personalized recommendations based on who you follow, making it easier to find new people you might like to follow, too. And as a little treat, there are explanations for wh", "id": 1288688, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/8/24265201/mastodon-4-3-update-grouped-notifications-design-discover-carousel", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Mastodon switches things up to make its app a little easier to use", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-08T15:12:25+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A Florida Army National Guard member works to remove debris in the Pass-A-Grille section of St. Petersburg ahead of Hurricane Milton\u2019s expected landfall in the middle of this week on October 7th, 2024, in Florida.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/aVqJG7zOXxY2hsB0Evi_urOJnlo=/0x0:3500x2333/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73640216/2176501056.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Bryan R. Smith / AFP via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"zfL4Yo\">The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) is fighting misinformation on top of a major storm cleanup in Florida <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/7/24264419/hurricane-milton-category-5-storm-rapid-intensification-climate-change\">as Hurricane Milton rapidly intensifies</a> just after Hurricane Helene rocked the state.</p>\n<p id=\"AWZhbR\">FEMA Administrator Deanne Criswell told reporters on a call Tuesday that misinformation around the storms is \u201cabsolutely the w", "id": 1288689, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/8/24265372/fema-misinformation-hurricane-helene-milton", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "FEMA adds misinformation to its list of disasters to clean up", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-08T15:09:18+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Chevy Bolt EUV\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/pqG-7QwC8jAmD91nCzBPW_yTAHY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73640203/ahawkins_220512_5248_0008.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Andrew J. Hawkins / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"8vK9p0\">General Motors teased some new details about the next-generation Chevy Bolt, which is expected to make its official debut later this year as a model year 2026 vehicle. </p>\n<p id=\"jN18dL\">At an investor event today, GM president Mark Reuss teased the new Bolt during a portion of the event in which the livestream was cut for \u201cconfidential\u201d reasons so that the company could show images of the still-unannounced vehicle. But Reuss\u2019 presentation could still be heard. </p>\n<p id=\"x1raTU\">Last year, GM said it was <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/4/25/23697356/gm-chevy-bolt-ev-euv-end-production\">discontinuing Bolt production</a> but later confirmed that it woul", "id": 1288690, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/8/24265404/gm-chevy-bolt-next-gen-charging-family-reuss", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "GM teases next-gen Chevy Bolt EV: faster charging, multiple models", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-08T14:44:47+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A normal ring, the Oura Ring Gen 3 (center), and the Oura Ring Gen 2 (left)\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/GiPVl0Flo6ZDRp92SGW9BePgQfY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73640108/vsong_2